"{\"uid\": \"ocregister.com-2024-08-03-katie-ledecky-makes-olympic-history-with-800-freestyle-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"e-Edition  Get the latest news delivered daily!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 47, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest news delivered daily!\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 87, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"e-Edition  Trending:  NANTERRE, France - Katie Ledecky capped another stellar Olympics by becoming only the second swimmer to win an event at four straight Summer Games, holding off Ariarne Titmus to win the 800-meter freestyle Saturday night.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 111, \"end\": 119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.9991092318230881, \"rank\": 0.0008915589821991726, \"text\": \"NANTERRE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 121, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.963692130326932, \"rank\": 0.030177601617059128, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 130, \"end\": 143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Ledecky's second gold medal in Paris and ninth of her remarkable career, which marked another milestone.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.068849755275419e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She became only the sixth Olympian to reach that figure, joining swimmer Mark Spitz, track star Carl Lewis, Soviet gymnast Larisa Latynina and Finnish runner Paavo Nurmi in a tie for second place.\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999478953346459, \"rank\": 5.2107380453226344e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 519, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Spitz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\"}, {\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.974882642732808e-12, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 569, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"score\": 0.999997220380235, \"rank\": 1.58007744505689e-06, \"text\": \"Finnish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\"}, {\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only athlete to win more golds: swimmer Michael Phelps with 23.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.376035090270229e-102, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put a lot of pressure on myself,\\\" Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just really happy that I could get the job done.\\\"\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky went faster than her winning time in Tokyo, touching in 8 minutes, 11.04 seconds.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 866, \"end\": 871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999961719368, \"rank\": 3.828262029131001e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, the Australian star known as the \\\"Terminator,\\\" was right on her shoulder nearly the entire race, but Ledecky pulled away in the final 100.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 911, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian star\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, who beat Ledecky in the 400 freestyle, took silver at 8:12.29.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to another American, Paige Madden at 8:13.00.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9991125807002037, \"rank\": 0.0008877437961948181, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that it was gonna be a tough race and I felt confident coming into it,\\\" Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I knew it was going to be tough no matter what, all the way down to the finish.\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I just had to stick in the race, trust myself, trust my training, trust that I know the hungry side of that.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, yeah, I am just kind of relieved.\\\"\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps had been the only swimmer to win the same event at four straight Olympics, taking gold in the 200 individual medley at Athens, Beijing, London and Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.999999070492754, \"rank\": 9.295077802296753e-07, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.070114404465687e-21, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4151775586171899e-24, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999924314192795, \"rank\": 3.8673808026094275e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1679, \"end\": 1693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3492106021172891e-23, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now he's got company.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky claimed her first gold with a surprise victory in the 800 free as a 15-year-old at the 2012 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky was thinking about that first gold before she dove in for No.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"9 - which came 12 years to the day of her breakout performance in London.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999924314192795, \"rank\": 3.8673808026094275e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One is the one that kind of means the most to me,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that August 3rd is the day I won in 2012 and I did not want August 3rd to be a day that I did not keep moving forward.\\\"\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No to worry.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has dominated the grueling race ever since - and is not done yet.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has made it clear she plans to keep swimming at least through the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not easy,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will take it year by year, and we will see if I can keep giving everything I have got for as long as I have left in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Summer McIntosh stamped herself as one of the swimming stars of the Paris Olympics with her third individual gold medal.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old Canadian chased down American Alex Walsh and held off another U.S. swimmer, Kate Douglass, to finish in an Olympic record of 2:06.56.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999985896607482, \"rank\": 1.4103265930540245e-06, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9991125807002037, \"rank\": 0.0008877437961948181, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 2715, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Douglass grabbed the silver in the star-studded final at 2:06.92, but the Americans lost the bronze when Walsh, the silver medalist in this event at Tokyo who recorded a time of 2:07.06, was disqualified because she did not finish the backstroke segment on her back.\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 3040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9982741663058516, \"rank\": 0.0017288173454009473, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999961719368, \"rank\": 3.828262029131001e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown, who touched fourth, was bumped up to the bronze at 2:08.08.\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a bitter blow for Walsh, whose younger sister, Gretchen, has won a gold medal and two silvers in Paris.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.260620982272169e-22, \"text\": \"Gretchen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 3216, \"end\": 3221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.068849755275419e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh set several world records ahead of the Paris Olympics, and she backed up the enormous expectations by claiming a starring role at La Defense Arena along with L\\u00e9on Marchand and Ledecky.\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3224, \"end\": 3232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999998958629, \"rank\": 1.0436278038724192e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh also won gold medals in the 200 butterfly and 400 IM, plus a silver in the 400 freestyle.\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3419, \"end\": 3427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999998958629, \"rank\": 1.0436278038724192e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She fell just 0.88 seconds - the margin of her loss to Ariarne Titmus - shy of matching Marchand's four individual golds.\", \"from\": 3518, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999999740794, \"rank\": 2.584620625072398e-11, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States made up for a disappointing showing in Tokyo by setting a world record in the 4\\u00d7100 mixed medley relay.\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999995930011, \"rank\": 3.1920373330058e-10, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3698, \"end\": 3703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999961719368, \"rank\": 3.828262029131001e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Murphy, Nic Fink, Gretchen Walsh and Torri Huske held off China for a winning time of 3:37.43, breaking the mark of 3:37.58 set by Britain when it won gold in the wild and woolly event's Olympic debut three years ago.\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 3986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3764, \"end\": 3775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.723792488163922e-16, \"text\": \"Ryan Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\"}, {\"begin\": 3827, \"end\": 3832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5716885259194066, \"rank\": 0.7457050925752668, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3900, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999786716958493, \"rank\": 2.132870566516481e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With each team picking two men and two women, the U.S. and China both went with their male swimmers in the first two legs.\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4047, \"end\": 4052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5716885259194066, \"rank\": 0.7457050925752668, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murphy put the U.S. in front on the backstroke, China's Qin Haiyang slipped past Nic Fink on the breaststroke, but Walsh put the Americans back in front on the butterfly before Huske held off Yang Junxuan to secure the gold.\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4336, \"entities\": [{\"begi